This Sunday, we ride for Monty. Please help me reach my fundraising goal! 

Margot’s bff Monty is the strongest - and happiest - little boy in the world. He was born with rare heart condition and had surgery just days after he was born. 

Today, Monty is thriving and it’s thanks to the strength of his parents (@carol.eliz.lee and Ryan) and the life-saving care of the doctors at CHOP. This Sunday, we ride for Monty and the incredible CHOP team.

Link to fundraiser in bio.

📸 @joefryernbc

Fantastic night at @sixthandi with my dear friend @jaketapper. We talked about his new book All the Demons are Here and much more! See the link in my bio for details about how to order your copy. It’s a page turner!
Congratulations to my friend @laurajarrett! I’m so excited to watch her and @peteralexandertv on @todayshow every Saturday!
I’m overcome with gratitude - to my @todayshow family in D.C. and NY - thank you for the most beautiful sendoff!
Starting September 17, it’s Meet the Press with @kristen.welker.⁠

Thank you @chucktodd for entrusting me with the honor of becoming the next moderator of @meetthepress. I have learned so much from you — you are the gold standard of political journalism. #ifitssunday

Kristen Welker will debut in the moderator seat on Meet The Press this Sunday. 

Before her rise as a White House Correspondent for NBC News, the Philly-native spent 5 years right here at NBC10. 

Be sure to tune in Sunday for Welker’s first show.

Former President Donald Trump told NBC’s @kristen.welker that Hunter Biden had the “deal of the century” before he was indicted.

“There’s no question about it,” Trump said. “He had a plea deal that was the deal of the century. The art of the deal — you could write a book on it.”

Hunter Biden was indicted on federal charges that he obtained a gun by falsely attesting that he was not using drugs. A plea deal he had negotiated with prosecutors fell apart earlier this year.

Watch the full interview Sunday on @meetthepress.

Former President Trump tells Kristen Welker that he was given an “option” to pardon himself before leaving office but didn’t take it in an exclusive interview with Meet the Press.⁠
⁠
“People said, ‘Would you like to pardon yourself?’ I had a couple of attorneys that said, ‘You can do it if you want,’” Trump said. “I had some people that said, ‘It would look bad if you do it, because I think it would look terrible.’”⁠
⁠
Trump recalled giving a decisive response at the time, in 2021: “Let me just tell you. I said, ‘The last thing I’d ever do is give myself a pardon.’”⁠
⁠
Watch MTP this Sunday for more from the exclusive interview. Check local listings.

In an exclusive interview with Meet the Press, former President Trump says allegations that he asked a staffer to delete video evidence from Mar-a-Lago are “false.”⁠
⁠
Kristen Welker: “Would you testify to that under oath?”⁠
⁠
Trump: “Sure.”⁠
⁠
Watch MTP this Sunday for more from the exclusive interview. Check local listings.

Former President Trump tells @kristen.welker that former first lady Melania Trump will be back on the campaign trail with him “pretty soon.”⁠
⁠
“She’s a private person, a great person, a very confident person and she loves our country very much,” Trump says.
⁠
“And honestly, I like to keep her away from it. It’s so nasty and so mean.”⁠
⁠
Tune in this Sunday for more from Welker’s exclusive interview with former President Donald Trump. Check local listings.

Former President Donald Trump tells @kristen.welker about the note he left for President Joe Biden as he was leaving the White House.

Watch the full interview tomorrow morning on @meetthepress.

Does Donald Trump lose sleep over the prospect of jail time?

“I don’t even think about it,” he tells @kristen.welker.

Watch the full interview this morning on @meetthepress.

Full story at the link in bio —⁠
⁠
The latest NBC News national poll shows former President Trump expanding his national lead in the Republican presidential nominating contest to more than 40 points over his nearest competition.⁠
⁠
It also has President Biden and Trump deadlocked in a hypothetical rematch more than a year before the general election. ⁠
⁠
Steve Kornacki joins Kristen Welker at the big board to explain.

Full story at the link in bio —⁠
⁠
In the latest NBC News national poll, President Biden’s job rating among registered voters stands at 41% approve and 56% disapprove — the highest disapproval rating of his presidency. ⁠
⁠
Deeper inside those numbers, Biden is underwater among voters between the ages of 18 and 34 (46% of them approve of his job performance), all women (46%), Latinos (43%) and independents (36%).⁠
⁠
What’s more, the NBC News poll finds 37% of voters approve of Biden’s handling of the economy, and 41% approve of his handling of foreign policy.

Full story at the link in bio —⁠
⁠
A combined 74% of registered voters in the latest NBC News poll say they have major concerns (59%) or moderate concerns (15%) that Biden, at age 80, doesn’t have the necessary mental and physical health to be president for a second term.⁠
⁠
According to the poll, 62% have either major concerns (52%) or moderate concerns (10%) about Trump facing different criminal and civil trials for alleged wrongdoing, including for trying to overturn the 2020 presidential election.⁠
⁠
Another 60% have major concerns (45%) or moderate concerns (15%) about Biden’s possible awareness or involvement in the business dealings of his son, Hunter, including alleged financial wrongdoing and corruption.

Rep. James Clyburn (D-S.C.), assistant House Democratic leader, stops short of calling Vice President Kamala Harris the future of the Democratic Party.⁠
⁠
“I look to her as a successor to this president. But I also know the history of that as well,” Clyburn tells moderator @kristen.welker.⁠
⁠
“It’s not a given. You don’t automatically move up. She’ll have to compete going forward with whoever may have dreams and aspirations.”

Secretary of State Antony Blinken said Sunday on #MTP that the U.S. is “actively working” to verify reports that Americans may be among the dead in the Israel-Hamas conflict, as well as reports that there could be some U.S. hostages.⁠
⁠
Hamas fighters on Saturday launched an attack on Israel through the country’s south. The ongoing attack has killed hundreds, and Hamas fighters have taken a number of civilians and soldiers hostage.⁠
⁠
More at the link in bio.

Voters in battleground Pennsylvania tell #MTP Moderator @Kristen.Welker how they’re feeling ahead of 2024 and the issues they care about heading into the election year. ⁠
⁠
Watch more at the link in bio.

Sen. Lindsey Graham (R-S.C.) announced a bipartisan trip to Israel and Saudi Arabia during an exclusive interview with #MTP. ⁠
⁠
“The drive to peace and normalization ... continues,” he told Kristen Welker. “There’s a desire of both parties to move forward.”⁠
⁠
Watch the full interview at the link in bio.

Sec. of State Antony Blinken says Israel has “absolutely no intent” to govern Gaza after the war with Hamas, telling @kristen.welker that “Israel can not go back to the status quo.”⁠
⁠
Watch the full interview at MeetThePress.com.⁠

I am thrilled to be honored as the 2023 Television Broadcast Honoree by @mmcadc during the 8th Annual Multicultural Media Correspondents Dinner on Monday, October 23! 
#mmcd2023 #mmca

Full interview at the link in bio —⁠
⁠
Rep. Pramila Jayapal (D-Wash.) said on #MTP that while she has been “one of President Biden’s biggest supporters,” she worries that the president’s response to Israel will cost him support from Arab and Muslim voters. ⁠

TONIGHT: Five candidates face off at the third Republican presidential debate in Miami, moderated by #MTP Moderator @kristen.welker, @nbcnightlynews Anchor Lester Holt and Hugh Hewitt, host of “The Hugh Hewitt Show” on Salem Radio Network.⁠
⁠
Watch it at 8 p.m. ET / 5 p.m. PT on NBC and streaming on NBC News NOW. ⁠
⁠
For more details on how to watch, head to the link in bio. ⁠

Israel Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu says “a different authority” must govern Gaza once its war with Hamas is over but won’t say if an international force should control the region.

Watch the full interview at the link in bio.

Sen. Joe Manchin (D-W.Va.) talks to Kristen Welker about the possibility of a possible presidential run following his announcement that he wouldn’t run for re-election.⁠
⁠
Watch the full interview at the link in bio.
Join us tomorrow for a special @meetthepress - we’ll hear from actor and advocate @selmablair. She is using her voice to advocate for the rights of those living with disabilities.

Actor and advocate Selma Blair sat down with Meet the Press Moderator Kristen Welker after her visit to the White House in October. 

She tells Kristen her message for lawmakers as she continues to fight for equity and accessibility. ⁠
⁠
Watch the full interview at the link in bio.

National Security Adviser Jake Sullivan on #MTP did not rule out the possibility of President Biden sending aid to Israel with conditions amid a four-day temporary cease-fire in the Israel-Hamas war with more hostages set to be released.⁠
⁠
Amid pressure from some Democrats who have expressed empathy toward Palestinians, Biden had said the question of aid to Israel with conditions is a “worthwhile thought.”⁠
⁠
More at the link in bio.

Join us for a jam-packed @meetthepress. We’ll have the latest from the Biden Administration on the Middle East plus an exclusive interview with @flgovrondesantis. And we’ll discuss the black maternal health crisis exclusively with @allysonfelix. Join us tomorrow!

FIRST TO NBC NEWS: National Security Council Coordinator for Strategic Communications John Kirby said Sunday on #MTP that the U.S. intelligence community has indicated that it was not aware of Hamas’ plan of attack on Israel.⁠
⁠
The New York Times recently reported that Israeli officials received Hamas’ plans for its Oct. 7 attack more than a year before it happened, citing documents, emails and interviews. The Times reported that the document was circulated among Israeli military and intelligence officials, but experts dismissed the plan as one that would be too difficult for Hamas to execute.⁠
⁠
More at the link in bio.

Gov. Ron DeSantis (R-Fla.) criticized the priorities of House Republicans as they look to a potential impeachment inquiry into President Joe Biden during an exclusive interview with Meet the Press.⁠
⁠
Watch the full interview at the link in bio.
Hope everyone’s holiday season is off to a bright start!! 🎄

Sen. Mitt Romney (R-Utah) explains why he hasn’t endorsed a 2024 presidential candidate and that he wants Senator Joe Manchin (D-W.Va.) to run for the Democratic nomination.⁠
⁠
Watch the full exclusive interview from Meet the Press at the link in bio. ⁠

Sen. Mitt Romney (R-Utah) reacts to comments made by former President Donald Trump on being a dictator on his first day in office if elected in 2024, calling Trump a “human gumball machine.”⁠
⁠
Watch the full exclusive interview at the link in bio.

I was honored this week to spend some time with our NBC affiliates in Michigan, Ohio, and Pennsylvania. I also sat down with voters in Michigan for an important conversation you’ll see Sunday on @meetthepress!

Meet the Press Moderator Kristen Welker spoke with a group of voters in Macomb County, Michigan, who previously voted for President Joe Biden. ⁠
⁠
She asked them to describe the president in one word. The responses: ⁠
⁠
“Tired,” “out of it,” “status quo” and “caring.”⁠
⁠
Watch more of their discussion at the link in bio.

I’m so proud to introduce a new segment to @meetthepress called “Meet the Moment” – interviews with influential voices outside of the political sphere who are speaking out on important issues and making a difference.

This Sunday, please tune in for my conversations with @selmablair, @allysonfelix , @masih.alinejad, and Tim Alberta.

This Sunday on @meetthepress, please join us for a full broadcast dedicated to mental health, what the Surgeon General called “the defining public health crisis of our time.”

I sat down with @senfettermanpa for a powerful interview on his own battle with clinical depression and how he was able to finally ask for help, checking himself into Walter Reed earlier this year. I’ll also be joined by @govcox and @govofco for a bipartisan conversation on this important subject.

During a special edition of #MTP, Sen. John Fetterman (D-Pa.) discusses his experience speaking publicly about his battle with depression and the uncertainty about how it would impact his career and family. ⁠
⁠
Watch the full interview at the link in bio.

TOMORROW: Watch exclusive interviews with @isaacherzog, @repstefanik (R-N.Y.) and Quentin Fulks.

#IfItsSunday

Advisers grappling with President Biden’s stubbornly low poll numbers and pressure from Democrats to shake up his strategy are planning a far more aggressive approach in coming weeks, with a keen focus on what they see as a high-stakes opportunity and hurdle to clear: ⁠
⁠
The State of the Union address.⁠
⁠
⁠
Read more from Mike Memoli and Kristen Welker at the link in bio.

Rep. Elise Stefanik (R-N.Y.) tells Kristen Welker that she will only commit to certifying the 2024 presidential election results if they are “constitutional.⁠”
⁠
During the interview on “Meet the Press,” Stefanik doubled down on disproven claims that the 2020 elections were “unconstitutional.”

On the road again, this time in New Hampshire to cover the nation's first presidential primary on Tuesday. Join us tomorrow for a special edition of #MTP with Gov. @rondesantis (R-Fla.), plus exclusive interviews with Gov. @chrissununu (R-N.H.) and @senatorhassan (D-N.H.) in Manchester.
#IfItsSunday
@meetthepress moderator, Philly Girl
